title: Push-Ups
about: There is no limit to how many push-ups one can do in a day. Many people do more than 300 push-ups a day.

title: Pull-Ups
about: In addition to working your back, pull-ups strengthen and sculpt your shoulders, forearms, and chest (pecs).

title: Squats
about: Squats burn calories and might help you lose weight. They also lower your chances of injuring your knees and ankles.

title: Handstand Push-Up
about: The obvious and primary benefit of handstand push-ups is increased upper body strength.

title: Dips
about: Bench dips can strengthen muscles in your triceps, chest, and shoulders. They're also simple to scale.

title: Shoulder Press
about: The shoulder press is one of the best exercises for strengthening your shoulders and upper back.
